# Hylleraas-Eckart closed-form precompilation cache (derivable from code)
geovac/_cache/

# Paper PDFs are TRACKED product artifacts (PI policy 2026-07-05): papers are
# the product; GitHub + Zenodo DOI snapshots must stay self-containedly readable.
# Refresh touched PDFs at each release.

# /qa calibration seed answer-keys — must NEVER be committed (QA hard rule)
debug/qa/*_seed_key.json

# REVTeX footnote sidecar files (auto-generated on every compile)
*Notes.bib

# Generated compile/test artifacts
debug/compile_output/
geovac/_archive/superseded/cache/
tests/_durations.json

# The viz/ web app uses a conventional src/lib/ source directory. The Python
# build-artifact rules above (lib/, build/, dist/ — all unanchored) would
# otherwise silently swallow it (they broke the v4.72.0 CI build). Re-include
# the web app's source tree; viz/ has its own .gitignore for node_modules/dist.
!viz/src/lib/
